# HCCA Cursor Rule

## Read Order
1. Read `README_FOR_CLAUDE.md` first.
2. Read only relevant files by directory map, avoid broad scanning.

## Architecture
- Keep one-way dependency: Router -> Service -> Model.
- Put permission checks only in router with `require_permission(...)`.
- Service layer assumes permission has passed.

## Async and DB
- Use `AsyncSession` for all DB access.
- Never use blocking calls in async code (`time.sleep`, sync HTTP).

## Schema and API
- Follow schema naming: `XxxCreate`, `XxxUpdate`, `XxxOut`, `XxxListItem`.
- Return schema object directly, do not wrap with `{ data, success }`.
- If API fields change, update `apps/web/src/lib/types.ts`.

## Migration Reminder
- If model/schema changes require DB DDL update, remind creating Alembic migration.

## Output Style
- Show only changed code sections.
- Keep edits minimal and focused.
